Index lookups are (O(logn)) -> tree structured

-> Vertical Scaling -> move to a bigger machine
-> Denormalization -> reads becomes less expensive but stale data is an issue.
-> Scale horizontally(read replicas or sharding) -> after 100k reads 
   -> Read Replicas -> leader(write comes here) and followers(service reads)
   -> Sharding -> (when data cannot be stored in one db hence read replicas are not useful) -> More common pattern for write
       -> Functional Sharding
       -> Slicing data based on Shard keys

-> Caching
  -> when you have skewed patterns to read 
      -> Application level caching -> add redis or memcached so reads, in front of dbs
      -> CDN's -> cache scaled across world -> best for media -> reduces latency due to closer to user.
 -> Drawback -> cache invalidation

