Celebrity Problem:
Hot key
 -> Request Coalscing -> for 500k only one db request
 -> Cache key fanout -> Shard Cache and spread hot keys TS:1 TS:2 ...TS:n

Cache Invalidation
 -> we have eventual consistency here how do we solve this
   -> Dont introduce cache
    -> if u still have a high throughput then we would have to cache
      -> if new data is written we can invalidate the cache 
        -> edge case when u have replicas and cache where new data is not written to all the replicas 
           and user goes and reads from that stale one, in that case we will end up serving with old data
            -> versioning comes to save here
               In the same transaction, we need to update the version in the cache and on the master DB.
               No one will read old data because in cache you will have the current latest version so any older version records in cache will
               just be skipped.
   


